  "slug": "paris-brest",
  "title": "Paris-Brest",
  "subtitle": "French choux pastry ring filled with hazelnut praline cream",
  "excerpt": "A large choux pastry ring piped and baked whole, split horizontally, and filled with a hazelnut praline cream. The pastry ring was created in 1910 to celebrate a Paris to Brest bicycle race; its wheel shape references the bicycle tyre. The choux must be fully dried in the oven to prevent collapse when cut. The praline cream is made from a hazelnut praline blended into whipped cream.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Paris-Brest was created in 1910 by pastry chef Louis Durand of Maisons-Laffitte, commissioned to celebrate the Paris-Brest-Paris cycling race. The recipe entered French patisserie literature widely by the 1920s. Auguste Escoffier, Le Guide Culinaire (1903 first edition, Project Gutenberg), gives the foundational choux pastry method (pate a choux) and mousseline cream on which Paris-Brest is built, though the assembled Paris-Brest post-dates that edition. The combination of choux, praline, and mousseline is documented in Henri-Paul Pellaprat, L'Art Culinaire Moderne (1936).",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Paris-Brest is a wheel-shaped choux ring filled with hazelnut praline cream. The choux is piped in a circle, baked until completely dry and deep gold, then split and filled. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "panade",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "Panade stage in choux pastry",
                  "termId": "cmpde3r2300006sv4l8a1cbwg"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " step (cooking the flour into the butter and water) must be done over heat until the dough pulls cleanly from the pan; underdone panade leads to flat choux. The ring must bake until very crisp inside to hold its shape when split. Serves 8."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Choux pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "water",
              "unit": "ml",
              "amount": 200
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "whole-milk",
              "unit": "ml",
              "amount": 50
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "unsalted-butter",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 100,
              "prepNote": "diced"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "salt-table",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 0.5
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "caster-sugar",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "plain-flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 150,
              "prepNote": "sifted"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "eggs",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 4,
              "prepNote": "beaten"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "almonds-flaked",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 30,
              "prepNote": "for sprinkling on top before baking"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hazelnut praline cream"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "hazelnuts",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 150,
              "prepNote": "skin-on, toasted and skins rubbed off"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "slug": "caster-sugar",
